title.narrative: Output 2.4: Strengthened capacity to implement the Safe School initiative.

description.narrative: UNICEF intensively supported the MoEC in responding to the COVID-19 pandemic in the education sector, focusing on development of regulations, cluster coordination, risk communication, distance learning and capacity development. ;The UNICEF support has contributed to continuity of learning among 45.6 million students during school closures and safe reopening of schools in low-risk zones during the pandemic situation. UNICEF also worked closely with local partners in Central Sulawesi and Nusa Tenggara Barat Provinces to support comprehensive school safety and adolescent resilience building programmes in disaster affected communities which reached over 22,000 children and adolescents. | Status:Met | As-of Date:03/12/2020
